Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
resizeBlackBox(25.10)                                    resizeBlackBox(25.10)

Name
       resizeBlackBox - Resizes a blackbox

Syntax
       resizeBlackBox

       <blackBoxName>

       [-help]

       [-width <width>]

       [-height <height>]

       [-aspectRatio <ratio>]

       Resizes a blackbox.

Parameters
       -aspectRatio <ratio>
              Specifies  the  new  aspect  ratio,  which  is height divided by
              width, with the blackbox area constant.

              Data_type: float, optional

       <blackBoxName>
              Specifies the name of the blackbox.

              Data_type: string, required

       -height <height>
              Specifies the new height in user units.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each  resizeBlackBox parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:

              man resizeBlackBox

       -width <width>
              Specifies the new width in user units.

              Data_type: float, optional

Examples
              * The following command resizes the height of blackbox1 to 600.5
                <mu>m. The width remains the same dimension.

                resizeBlackBox blackbox1 -height 600.5

              * The  following  command  resizes the height of blackbox2 to be
                twice as long as its width. The area remains the same.

                resizeBlackBox blackbox2 -aspectRatio 2

Related Information
              * specifyBlackBox

              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

